<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kwisst</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-24 10:25:01</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is a good demonstration of the absurd amounts of spare cash floating around the mature servers. The Bracer is basically of little real value, and just has a novelty effect that can be fun to play with for non-casters. But it is rare, despite dropping in one of the best mid-twenties hunting zones, and there are plenty of people willing to blow a lot of cash on a useless but rare item</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ailee Heartseeker</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-11 21:18:51</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Umm folks how many times have you had to follow group members thru hostile terrain while invis? Carry this Bracer and invis potions and you are set for all emergencies as a non-caster. Dont wear the silly thing during combat. Equip it while doing sneaky invis things, right-click on yourself and any other group members that need see invis, replace it with your normal bracer, and you are good to go. This item is an excellent tool for warriors and such.<BR>
<BR>
Stuff I carry:<BR>
Bracer of the hidden<BR>
Invis potions<BR>
Sow potions<BR>
Pumice stones<BR>
1 Emergency Gate potion<BR>
Iksar Ceremonial BP<BR>
Shrunken Goblin skull earring<BR>
<BR>
(see the flexibility a warrior can have on extended trips?)<BR>
<BR>
On a lighter note, havent you had annoying casters who are invised /bonking you and such? Shock the crap out of them and lay a crippling bonk on them. </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
